Board Game Rules – Setting Obstacles and Figures
1. Game Boards and Obstacles

The game board comes in three sizes:

Small Board (12×12) has 18 obstacles: 2 Caves, 2 Trees, 2 Rocks, 4 Lakes, 3 Rivers, 3 Canyons, 2 MysteryBoxes.



Medium Board (12×16) has 20 obstacles: 2 Caves, 3 Trees, 3 Rocks, 4 Lakes, 3 Rivers, 3 Canyons, 2 MysteryBoxes.

Large Board (12×20) has 24 obstacles: 2 Caves, 3 Trees, 3 Rocks, 5 Lakes, 4 Rivers, 4 Canyons, 3 MysteryBoxes.

Obstacle Rules:

Cave: Any figure entering a cave can exit from any other cave on the board.

Tree, Rock, River, Lake, Canyon: Movement restrictions vary by figure (see section 4).

MysteryBox: Special interactive square with effects depending on game variant or player rules.

2. Figures and Starting Positions

Figures are arranged in three lines:

Topline (12–20–24 units depending on board size): Ram-Tower, Chariot, Saboteur, Paladin, Vezier, Monarch, Duchess, Druid, Paladin, Saboteur, Chariot, Ram-Tower.

Semi-Topline (11–19–23 units): 12 Hoplites.

Semi-Bottomline (2 units): 12 Hoplites.

Bottomline (1 unit): Ram-Tower, Chariot, Saboteur, Paladin, Vezier, Monarch, Duchess, Druid, Paladin, Saboteur, Chariot, Ram-Tower.

3. Figures – Points Value

Monarch: 210 points

Duchess: 27 points

Ram-Tower: 20 points

Chariot: 16 points (Zompie Mode: 13)

Paladin: 15 points (Zompie Mode: 12)

Saboteur: 12 points (Zompie Mode: 9)

Druid/Necromancer: 13 points

Vezier/Warlock: 11 points

Hoplite: 3 points

Notes:

Necromancer can revive units (Ram, Chariot, Bomber, Paladin) if Monarch, Duchess, and Warlock are in their original positions.

Revived units may have reduced attack capabilities.

Zompie Mode applies a weaker point value after revival.

4. Figures – Movement, Attack, and Abilities

Hoplite:

Moves 3 steps forward on the first move, then 2 steps.

Shoots sideways 1 step.

Can pass through caves.

Cannot pass through rivers, lakes, or canyons.

Ram-Tower:

Moves in a cross (orthogonal) pattern any number of steps.

Shoots up to 5 steps in a cross pattern.

Cannot pass through obstacles unless specified.

Chariot:

Moves in L-shaped corners (2-1, 1-2, 2-2, 3-1, 1-3 steps).

Can pass over other figures.

Units killed by Chariot cannot be revived until Chariot is destroyed.

Shoots only in 4-step corner range.

Can pass through rivers (2 steps wide).

Cannot pass through lake, canyon, or cave.

Bomber:

Moves 1 or 2 steps in cross or X patterns.

Cannot shoot or attack directly.

Placing Bomber triggers explosives in a 2-step radius affecting same-type figures.

Can pass through rivers (1 step wide), caves, and canyons.

Cannot pass through lakes.

Paladin:

Moves sideways any number of steps.

Shoots up to 3 steps sideways.

Can pass through rivers (1 step wide), caves, and canyons.

Cannot pass through lakes.

Warlock (Vezier):

Moves in 2-step corner patterns.

Can pass over figures in its path.

Can swap positions with any Hoplite or the Monarch.

Can pass through lakes and caves.

Cannot pass through rivers or canyons.

Monarch:

Moves 1 step in any direction.

Shoots 1 step in any direction.

Can pass through caves.

Cannot pass through rivers, lakes, or canyons.

Duchess:

Moves in any direction.

Shoots up to 9 steps in any direction.

Can pass through rivers.

Cannot pass through lakes, canyons, or caves.

Necromancer (Druid):

Moves in any direction.

Shoots 1 step normally, or freeze-stuns up to 8 steps (reduced by 2 per revival).

Can revive Ram, Chariot, Bomber, or Paladin if Monarch, Duchess, and Warlock are in original positions.

Revived units may have limited attack range; Bomber can attack normally as Zompie.

Can pass through lakes and caves.

Cannot pass through rivers or canyons.

5. Special Rules

Caves: Entering a cave allows exit from any other cave on the board.

Explosions: Bomber affects same-type figures in a 2-step radius.

Revival: Necromancer can revive certain units; revived units may have limited abilities.

Zompie Mode: Some figures have reduced points after revival.